HEADWORD: Pavesade
<hw>Pav`e*sade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Pavise</er>.]</ety> <def>A canvas screen, formerly sometimes
extended along the side of a vessel in a naval engagement, to conceal
from the enemy the operations on board.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

